Author: BARKER
Vol / Page: 20
Edition:
Quote: `The `Pilgrims,' as the first comers are always called. I like the name; it is so pretty and suggestive.'
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1877
Source: Colonial Experiences
Author: PRATT
Vol / Page: 234
Edition:
Quote:  In the `Dream of a Shagroon', which bore the date Ko Matinau, April 1851, and which first appearted in the `Wellington Spectator' of May 7, the term `Pilgrim' was first applied to the settlers; it was also predicted in it that the `Pilgrims' would be `smashed', and the Shagroons left in undisputed possession of the country for their flocks and herds.'
